d in my envision schools projects i spend time with my education pioneers cohort the cohort includes 40 graduate students who are tackling education projects throughout the bay area and sacramento we convene formally for professional development seminars where we share project updates and suggestions as well as meet alums and industry leaders we also talk throughout the summer at small group dinners conference calls and informal events to build community with one another the cohort experience allows me to gain a much broader richer understanding of the education landscape both nationally and within california breadth with depth my ideal summer learn more about envision schools http www envisionschools org learn more about education pioneers http www educationpioneers org luke pena post new comment subject comment input format filtered html web page addresses and e mail addresses turn into links automatically allowed html tags a em strong cite code ul ol li dl dt dd lines and paragraphs break automatically full html web page addresses and e mail addresses turn into links automatically you may use swf file song mp3 to display flash files inline more information about formatting options captcha this question is for testing whether you are a human visitor and to prevent automated spam submissions math question 16 3 solve this simple math problem and enter the result eg for 1 3 enter 4 bloggers executive director's column kriss deiglmeier social innovation fellows puentes global mba students groups new orleans entrepreneurship week post class summer interns water service learning trip south africa service learning trip events tedx silicon valley usrio 2.0 all blogs blog roll barefoot mba next billion global voices innovation cfed rugaba kanani lessons from africa pop tech social edge stanford social innovation review opinion blog ted admissions faculty & research alumni recruiters & companies giving executive education news about the gsb copyright 2009 stanford graduate 